title: System Analysis and Design
details: System analysis and design is a process that many companies use to evaluate particular business situations and develop ways to improve them through more optimal methods.

title: Artificial Intelligence
details: Artificial intelligence (AI), the ability of a digital computer or computer-controlled robot to perform tasks commonly associated with intelligent beings.

title: Electrical Engineering
details: Engineering involves the application of the principles of science and mathematics to solve real world problems and to innovate new products and processes across a wide range of industries and applications.

title: Object-Oriented Programming in C++
details: Object-oriented programming (OOP) is a computer programming model that organizes software design around data, or objects, rather than functions and logic.

title: Web Technology
details: Web Technology refers to the various tools and techniques that are utilized in the process of communication between different types of devices over the internet.

title: Operating System
details: An Operating System (OS) is a software that acts as an interface between computer hardware components and the user.
